      "title": "Why Shrink at 1/4, Not 1/2?",
      "type": "step-diagram",
      "description": "Avoiding thrashing with proper shrink threshold",
      "steps": [
        {
          "step": 1,
          "label": "Bad: Shrink at 1/2",
          "visual": "Cap=8, Size=4 \u2192 Add \u2192 Cap=8, Size=5\n\u2192 Remove \u2192 Cap=4, Size=4 (shrink!)\n\u2192 Add \u2192 Cap=8, Size=5 (grow!)\n\u2192 Remove \u2192 Cap=4, Size=4 (shrink!)\n... infinite loop!",
          "note": "Constant grow/shrink at boundary"
        },
        {
          "step": 2,
          "label": "Good: Shrink at 1/4",
          "visual": "Cap=8, Size=4 \u2192 Remove \u2192 Cap=8, Size=3\n\u2192 Remove \u2192 Cap=8, Size=2 (shrink to 4)\n\u2192 Add \u2192 Cap=4, Size=3\n\u2192 Add \u2192 Cap=4, Size=4\n\u2192 Add \u2192 Cap=8, Size=5 (grow)",
          "note": "Buffer zone prevents thrashing"
